{
  "type": "spell",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ddb\">\n<p>A 20-foot-radius &amp;Reference[sphere]{sphere} of whirling air springs into existence centered on a point you choose within range. The &amp;Reference[sphere]{sphere} remains for the spell’s duration. Each creature in the &amp;Reference[sphere]{sphere} when it appears or that ends its turn there must succeed on a &amp;Reference[str]{Strength} saving throw or take 2d6 &amp;Reference[bludgeoning]{bludgeoning} damage. The sphere’s space is difficult terrain.</p>\n<p>Until the spell ends, you can use a bonus action on each of your turns to cause a bolt of &amp;Reference[lightning]{lightning} to leap from the center of the &amp;Reference[sphere]{sphere} toward one creature you choose within 60 feet of the center. Make a ranged spell attack. You have advantage on the attack roll if the target is in the &amp;Reference[sphere]{sphere}. On a hit, the target takes 4d6 &amp;Reference[lightning]{lightning} damage.</p>\n<p>Creatures within 30 feet of the &amp;Reference[sphere]{sphere} have disadvantage on &amp;Reference[wis]{Wisdom} (&amp;Reference[prc]{Perception}) checks made to listen.</p>\n<p><em><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong></em> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 5th level or higher, the damage increases for each of its effects by 1d6 for each slot level above 4th.</p>\n</div>",
      "chat": ""
    },
